				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Well good for two thirds of the networks.  
<br />

<br />
If the commercial in question had stopped at simply advertizing it's acceptance, it would be unobjectionable.
<br />

<br />
The the majority of the commercial is dedicated to footage featuring large, intimidating men dressed in black and muscle shrits pushing away gays from a velvet rope.  This footage implies that most churches actively exclude gays and will not accept them.  
<br />

<br />
This image is misleading and incorrect.  Most churches do not exclude gays.  Churches who deem homosexuality as a sin have almost always accpeted them as members.  Embrace the sinner and not the sin has been thier motto.
<br />

<br />
The basic message of the ad is misleading and inflammatory.  It will upset a lot of mainstream practicioners since it casts thier religion in a false light.  
<br />

<br />
Again, had the ad simply portrayed the Church of Christ in a favorable light, it would have been fine.  But it cut down other mainstream religions by implication -- and in a misleading way.  Airing it would piss a lot of people off, and would hurt marketshare. 
<br />

<br />
Simply put, the ad promotes an agenda in a misleading fashion and the networks exercised sound judgment in choosing not to air it.<br />_________________<br />Old Bard of Brell
<br />
Proud Member of Poison Arrow</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
