			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">McBash, you do realize just saying "THEY ARE BUSINESSES" isn't the beginning and end of it.
<br />

<br />
Remember, the broadcast media have special responsibility because they use a limited resource as their medium - radio waves. And you or I do not have the right to set up a competing broadcast station on their airspace, the FCC will slap us down for that. 
<br />

<br />
So the covenant is that the broadcast media outlets have a greater responsibility than the print media do, because they are using airwaves owned by the public. 
<br />

<br />
All that aside, of course, any media network that makes a decision, whether for ZOMG BUSINESS reasons or moral reasons, must face the consequence of that decision. To say we should all shut up because the media networks have the "right" to accept whatever advertising they choose is missing the point. They also have to face the consequences of their choices.
<br />

<br />
And the negative publicity is definitely a consequence.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
