				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Well first of all, the equal protection clause does not apply here.  The equal protection clause mandates that the laws of a state must treat an individual in the same manner as others in similar conditions and circumstances.  Since there is no state action in this case, your reference to this clause is meaningless.
<br />

<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">You're hacking at this commercial because it makes misleading comparisons with other churches, but yet, you remain silent and everything's A-OK when one company selling a physical product makes misleading comparisons with other companies that sell a similar product. </td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
