Not quite.  I do not like this ad because it is misleading, but moreso because it implies other mainstream churches will not accept homosexuals and ethnic minorities.  I suppose I am also bothered by the fact that the UCC doesn't have the stones to even name the religions it impugns.  
<br />

<br />
I also suppose if Coke implied it was better than Pepsi because Pesi forbade blacks and women from using thier product, I would be somewhat bothered by that, too, and more than a little bewildered.  But I also recognize that religion is not a product and that worship is something more than mere brand loyalty.  You do not.  That's where we are going to have to agree to disagree and move on.<br />_________________<br />Old Bard of Brell
