				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Partha, two questions.
<br />

<br />
1.  Does the phrase "equal treatment under the law" have any meaning or application outside of an equal protection clause analysis?
<br />

<br />
2.  If so, what is that meaning or application?
<br />

<br />
Partha, "equal treatment under the law" and the equal protection clause are the same thing.  Just like the establishment clause and "separation of church and state" are the same thing, just worded differently.
<br />

<br />
Don't play gotcha unless you know what you are talking about.<br />_________________<br />Old Bard of Brell
<br />
Proud Member of Poison Arrow</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
