				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Equal protection clause is not a catchall for every single point by which we presume to treat things equally, AFAIC. Then again, I'm not playing legal hairsplitter. I'm simply saying that if you as a business are going to treat one type of ad a certain way in regards to it's suitability, you have to treat them all with that standard. To do otherwise, ESPECIALLY if you're doing it as federally regulated media - is a despicable act.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
