				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody"></span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Relbeek Einre wrote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">McBash, you do realize just saying "THEY ARE BUSINESSES" isn't the beginning and end of it.
<br />

<br />
Remember, the broadcast media have special responsibility because they use a limited resource as their medium - radio waves. And you or I do not have the right to set up a competing broadcast station on their airspace, the FCC will slap us down for that. 
<br />

<br />
So the covenant is that the broadcast media outlets have a greater responsibility than the print media do, because they are using airwaves owned by the public. 
<br />

<br />
All that aside, of course, any media network that makes a decision, whether for ZOMG BUSINESS reasons or moral reasons, must face the consequence of that decision. To say we should all shut up because the media networks have the "right" to accept whatever advertising they choose is missing the point. They also have to face the consequences of their choices.
<br />

<br />
And the negative publicity is definitely a consequence.</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
The ONLY consequences are business ones.  And sorry Chants, right and wrong are in no way shape or form media's business.  You take away advertizers, you destroy and anihilate all the media outlets in question here.  The 'right' they chase is simply the one that has the least negative or most favorable impact on the amount of persons reached by their product.
<br />

<br />
I really dont care what consequences these destoyers of free will suffer, but dont for a second hold them up to any level of scrutiny regarding the truth, truth is subjective, and if it sells more doritos, its truth today.
<br />

<br />
They may regurgitate an unimpeachable fact now and then, so long as toyotas flow, they can tolerate it.
<br />

<br />
As far as the FCC goes, I know you know there isnt a snowballs chance in hell they are coming into play over something liken this.
<br />

<br />
BUSINESSES, regardless of what you beatiful dreamers want to think, your argument and protests stops dead at that single fact, and your outrage against this particular machine is long overdue.
<br />

<br />
